Simple IOCTL Character Driver
 Description

This Linux kernel module implements a character device driver with an IOCTL interface.
It allows user-space applications to set and get an integer variable inside the kernel using ioctl() system calls.

Skills Covered

Implementing unlocked_ioctl() in kernel modules

Defining and using IOCTL macros (_IOW, _IOR)

Exchanging data between user space and kernel space using copy_to_user() and copy_from_user()
